narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: i would only recommend this course to a student interested in making hollywood-style films with little to no film background.
A phenomenal course which introduces students to the world of film, looking at many facets of the filmmaking world.
This class goes over all aspects of shooting a scene: writing, script analysis, camera movement, directing actors etc. It is focused almost exclusively on narrative film.

Do a small amount of reading and write weekly reading responses (minimal time involved), make about 6 prompted short films, spend entire class reviewing that week's films. I would probably not take the class.

Learning how to make an video worth watching.What makes a video interesting. What are the beginner's mystakes to avoir. How do you use a camera, a boom, final cut pro 7, write a script, interprete a script and direct actors.Recommend it.
